Quote: <br>
&quot;Perhaps these mobs are a specific issue that should be addressed. Anyway, I also wonder how well you are managing your mana pool and med time, and whether you realize that with proper mana regen, you'll be able to do a lot more than just use your velk robe in the last 25 minutes of a half hour fight. If you can get your standing regen to 25 points per tick(clarity2(11) and bard song(14)), then over 30 minutes you'll have 7500 mana, not counting the 2700-3000 stored mana that you burn in the first 5 minutes. If you can manage to meditate, you'll have a lot more mana than that. There still might be a problem with damage output on these big unbanable mobs, but please don't try to exaggerate things by claiming that you can be oom and useless but for a robe for 25 whole minutes.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, Did it again tonight and the following happened (had c3 and bard song):<br>
<br>
1. Emptied my mana onto the mob within 5 mins.  This was alternating SS and robe to try to minimise agro.<br>
2. Casted robe for another 20 mins whilst regening mana standing up<br>
3. Had a full bar of mana to burn away again in the last few minutes of the fight.  In which time I chained SS and concussion one after the other.<br>
<br>
Please think about what that means.  For 20 minutes of the fight I was down to casting the velk robe at 40 dps where a melee is chugging away for the full fight at whatever a decent equipped melee fights for (100dps?)<br>
<br>
That is still appalling and is not exaggerating at all.<br>
<br>
Now I'd be interested to see the dmg logs of any other class.  Assuming no one died all melee classes will out damage a wizard by at least 100%.  <br>
<br>
There is no &quot;there still might be a problem&quot; - there is a definate problem.  I just wish I had the data to back it up but its pretty obvious imo just thinking about it logically.<br>
<br>
oh btw, just in case you didn't know the velk robe is a 15/16 sec cast so you can't med during its casting (although you used to be able to due to a bug). Also sit agro is a factor, so using a velk robe for a wizard IS the most efficient use of mana over time (or VP robe).<br>
<br>
